tupid. Don't take <br />my word for it? Look for them. And see them do things like<br /><br /> - drivers/scsi/arm/fas216.h:<br /><br />	#ifndef NO_IRQ<br />	#define NO_IRQ 255<br />	#endif<br /><br /> - drivers/pcmcia/pd6729.c (really interesting):<br /><br />	#ifndef NO_IRQ<br />	#define NO_IRQ  ((unsigned int)(0))<br />	#endif<br /><br /> - drivers/rtc/rtc-m48t59.c:<br /><br />	#ifndef NO_IRQ<br />	#define NO_IRQ  (-1)<br />	#endif<br /><br />so please don't add yet another version to the insanity. Just mark <br />anything with NO_IRQ as BROKEN or ARM-specific, or something.<br /><br />		Linus<br /><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
